data.chText: 贪污的；受贿的；腐败的；营私舞弊的
data.enText: willing to use their power to do dishonest or illegal things in return for money or to get an advantage

data.chText: 整个体系都效率低下并且腐败堕落。
data.enText: The whole system is inefficient and corrupt.

data.chText: 已变换的；有缺陷的；有错误的
data.enText: containing changes or faults, and no longer in the original state

data.chText: 这张磁盘上的文件好像有错误。
data.enText: The text on the disk seems to be corrupt.
to have a bad effect on sb and make them behave in an immoral or dishonest way

data.chText: 权力与野心使他腐化堕落。
data.enText: He was corrupted by power and ambition.
the corrupting effects of great wealth
to change the original form of sth, so that it is damaged or spoiled in some way

data.chText: 引起（计算机文件等的）错误；破坏
data.enText: to cause mistakes to appear in a computer file, etc. with the result that the information in it is no longer correct

data.chText: 这程序莫名其妙地导致了系统文件出错。
data.enText: The program has somehow corrupted the system files.

data.chText: 磁盘如果过载，数据就会出错。
data.enText: The disk will corrupt if it is overloaded.

simple_means.memory_skill: cor 加强 + rupt 破，断裂 → 破坏组织肌体 → 腐败的

means: 引起(计算机文件等的)错误

tr: place under suspicion or cast doubt upon
make illegal payments to in exchange for favors or influence
corrupt morally or by intemperance or sensuality
example: debauch the young people with wine and women
Socrates was accused of corrupting young men
Do school counselors subvert young children?
humanity they knew to be corrupt...from the day of Adam's creation
a corrupt and incompetent city government
spoke a corrupted version of the language

value.def: Someone who is corrupt behaves in a way that is morally wrong, especially by doing dishonest or illegal things in return for money or power.

example.ex: ...to save the nation from corrupt politicians of both parties...
example.tran: 从两个政党的腐败政客手中挽救这个国家

example.ex: He had accused three opposition members of corrupt practices.
example.tran: 他指控3名反对派成员营私舞弊。

value.tran: 腐败的;贪污的;受贿的;营私舞弊的

example.ex: ...several government officials charged with acting corruptly.
example.tran: 被控营私舞弊的几名政府官员

value.def: If someone is corrupted by something, it causes them to become dishonest and unjust and unable to be trusted.

example.ex: It is sad to see a man so corrupted by the desire for money and power.
example.tran: 看到一个人因为追逐金钱和权力而如此腐化真是悲哀。

value.def: To corrupt someone means to cause them to stop caring about moral standards.

example.ex: ...warning that television will corrupt us all...
example.tran: 警告说电视将会使我们所有人堕落
残暴行为会使人堕落、道德败坏。

value.def: If something is corrupted, it becomes damaged or spoiled in some way.

example.ex: Some of the finer typefaces are corrupted by cheap, popular computer printers...
example.tran: 有些比较优美的字体经过价廉、通用的电脑打印机处理后就面目全非了。

example.ex: They can ensure that traditional cuisines are not totally corrupted by commercial practices.
example.tran: 他们可以确保传统烹饪不会被商业运营模式完全破坏。
